# Thailian.com Frontend Rules

## Tech Stack
- Next.js (App Router)
- React, TypeScript
- Tailwind CSS
- framer-motion (for micro-animations and heavy-equipment reveals)
- lucide-react (for iconography)

## Coding Guidelines
- **Strictly provide ACTUAL CODE when fixing or explaining. No high-level abstractions.**
- Maximize Server Components to optimize SEO and initial load times. Use `"use client"` only for interactive elements (animations, state, forms).
- Use `shadcn/ui` conventions for robust, accessible UI components.
- Components live in `@/components/{ui,sections,layouts}/`.
- Always satisfy strict TypeScript requirements.
- Add meaningful Metadata for every page route to boost SEO.

## Design Aesthetic & "Wow" Factor
- **Visual Excellence is mandatory.** Use sleek dark modes, glassmorphism, and structured gradients.
- **Typography:** Avoid defaults. Rely on premium Google Fonts (e.g., Inter, Outfit) initialized in `layout.tsx`.
- **Dynamic Feedback:** Buttons and interactive elements must have smooth hover/focus transitions.
- **Animations:** Use `framer-motion` for staggering list views (e.g., forklift catalogs) and creating cinematic hero sections.

## Assets
- NEVER use blank box placeholders. Always use or generate realistic images (e.g., forklift 3D renders, warehouse backgrounds) if needed during development.
